LDG_ERROR(3)                  LDG Call                   LDG_ERROR(3)

NAME
   ldg_error() - report a code error when ldg_open() returns NULL.

SYNOPSYS
   #include <ldg.h>

   int ldg_error( void);

PARAMETER
    return : an error code.

DESCRIPTION
    This function returns  an error code  if ldg_open() returns  NULL.
    Possible errors are :

      ú LDG_LIB_FULLED: Impossible to register a new library,
      ú LDG_APP_FULLED: Impossible to register a new client,
      ú LDG_ERR_EXEC:   the LDG-library requested is not GEMDOS executable,
      ú LDG_BAD_FORMAT: the LDG-library requested have a bad format,
      ú LDG_LIB_LOCKED: the LDG-library requested is locked,
      ú LDG_NOT_FOUND:  the LDG-library requested is not found,
      ú LDG_NO_MEMORY:  no more memory,
      ú LDG_NO_TSR:     TSR not installed,
      ú LDG_BAD_TSR:    bad TSR version number (function required not
                        supported by TSR).

COMPATIBILITY LDG 1.xx
    Some  errors   are  obsolets   with  LDG   2.00:   LDG_NO_MANAGER,
    LDG_TIME_IDL With LDG 1.xx,  ldg_error can return  0 even when  an
    error occurs.  In  this case,  the  LDG-manager sends  a  message,
    LDG_ERROR, indicating the error.                                  

SEE ALSO
    ldg_open(3).
    